cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DS 

This paper discusses the behavior of dropout in deep networks, which is a popular regularization technique in machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) since these fields heavily use deep networks. The paper also discusses the behavior of dropout in relation to weight decay, which is a common regularization technique in optimization, so cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely sub-category. Finally, the paper involves analyzing data and uncovering new properties, so cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible sub-category as well.
